---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const effectiveDate = '2026-07-17';
const lastUpdated = 'July 17, 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Diamond Dot Art - LOEF Studio"
  description="Privacy Policy for the Diamond Dot Art mobile application by LOEF Studio. Learn what data the app collects, how advertising and subscriptions work, and how to exercise your privacy rights."
  url="https://loefstudio.com/privacy/"
>
  <Header />

  <main class="policy-page">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="policy-header">
        <span class="subtitle">LEGAL</span>
        <h1 class="policy-title">Privacy <span class="text-gradient">Policy</span></h1>
        <div class="section-line"></div>
        <p class="policy-meta">
          Effective date: <time datetime={effectiveDate}>{lastUpdated}</time>
        </p>
      </header>

      <article class="policy-card cozy-card">
        <p class="lead">
          This Privacy Policy applies to the <strong>Diamond Dot Art</strong> app for mobile devices, together with
          any related services operated by JUNG YEOL LEE (LOEF Studio) (collectively, the "Application").
          JUNG YEOL LEE is hereby referred to as the "Service Provider".
        </p>

        <section>
          <h2>No Account Required</h2>
          <p>
            The Application does not offer or require account registration. You do not create a username or
            password, and the Service Provider does not ask you for your name, email address, phone number, or
            other directly identifying information in order to use the Application. Your game progress is stored
            on your device and, if you have enabled it, in your personal Apple iCloud account, which is
            controlled by you and not by the Service Provider.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Information Collection and Use</h2>
          <p>
            The Service Provider does not operate its own analytics servers and does not collect your game
            progress or gameplay history. The information described below is collected by the advertising service
            the Application uses, and may include:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Your device's Internet Protocol (IP) address, and the coarse location derived from it</li>
            <li>Your mobile operating system version and device model</li>
            <li>Your advertising identifier (IDFA), where you have permitted tracking</li>
            <li>Your interactions with the advertisements shown in the Application</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            This information is used to deliver, measure, and improve the advertising shown in the Application, as
            described in the "Advertising" section below. Because the Application has no sign-up, the Service
            Provider does not ask you to provide personally identifiable information such as your name, birth
            date, or gender.
          </p>
          <p>
            Separately, Apple may provide the Service Provider with aggregated statistics and crash reports
            through App Store Connect, based on the analytics settings you control on your device in
            <strong>Settings &rsaquo; Privacy &amp; Security &rsaquo; Analytics &amp; Improvements</strong>. This
            information is aggregated by Apple and does not identify you individually.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Advertising</h2>
          <p>
            The Application displays advertisements through <strong>Google AdMob</strong>. To serve, measure, and
            improve these advertisements, AdMob and its partners may collect and process information such as your
            advertising identifier (IDFA), IP address, device and operating system information, coarse location
            derived from your IP address, and your interactions with ads.
          </p>
          <p>
            On iOS, the Application will ask for your permission through Apple's App Tracking Transparency (ATT)
            prompt before your advertising identifier is used to track you across apps and websites owned by other
            companies. If you decline, you will still see ads, but they will be less relevant to you. You can
            change this choice at any time in
            <strong>Settings &rsaquo; Privacy &amp; Security &rsaquo; Tracking</strong> on your device, or limit ad
            personalization in <strong>Settings &rsaquo; Privacy &amp; Security &rsaquo; Apple Advertising</strong>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Where required by applicable law (for example, in the European Economic Area and the United Kingdom),
            the Application presents a consent message before non-essential advertising and measurement
            technologies are used, and you may change or withdraw your consent from within the Application.
          </p>
          <p>
            You can learn more about how Google uses information from apps that use its services at
            <a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Subscriptions and Purchases</h2>
          <p>
            The Application offers optional paid subscriptions (for example, an ad-free experience and additional
            content). All subscriptions are sold and processed by <strong>Apple</strong> through the App Store using
            your Apple Account.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              The Service Provider <strong>never receives or stores your payment card number, billing address, or
              Apple Account credentials</strong>. Payment is handled entirely by Apple.
            </li>
            <li>
              The Application receives a transaction receipt and subscription status from Apple in order to
              validate your purchase and unlock the features you paid for. This information is associated with
              your device and purchase, not with a registered account.
            </li>
            <li>
              Subscriptions renew automatically unless cancelled at least 24 hours before the end of the current
              period. You can view, manage, or cancel your subscription at any time in
              <strong>Settings &rsaquo; [your name] &rsaquo; Subscriptions</strong> on your device.
            </li>
            <li>
              Refunds are handled by Apple in accordance with Apple's policies. Requests can be submitted at
              <a href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://reportaproblem.apple.com</a>.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Apple's handling of your purchase data is governed by Apple's Privacy Policy at
            <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
          <p>
            The Application or its third-party SDKs may use cookies, SDKs, pixels, and similar technologies to
            support functionality, advertising, or service delivery. Where required by applicable law,
            the Service Provider will obtain consent before using non-essential tracking technologies.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Third Party Access</h2>
          <p>
            Aggregated and anonymized data may be periodically transmitted to external services to help the
            Service Provider improve the Application and its service. The Service Provider may share your
            information with third parties only in the ways described in this privacy statement.
          </p>
          <p>
            Please note that the Application utilizes third-party services that have their own privacy policies
            about handling data. Below are links to the privacy policies of the third-party service providers used
            by the Application:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Google AdMob &mdash;
              <a href="https://support.google.com/admob/answer/6128543" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://support.google.com/admob/answer/6128543</a>
            </li>
            <li>
              Apple (App Store, iCloud) &mdash;
              <a href="https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://www.apple.com/legal/privacy</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>The Service Provider may disclose automatically collected information:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>as required by law, such as to comply with a subpoena, or similar legal process;</li>
            <li>
              when they believe in good faith that disclosure is necessary to protect their rights, protect your
              safety or the safety of others, investigate fraud, or respond to a government request;
            </li>
            <li>
              with their trusted service providers who work on their behalf, do not have an independent use of the
              information the Service Provider discloses to them, and have agreed to adhere to the rules set forth
              in this privacy statement.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>International Data Transfers</h2>
          <p>
            The Service Provider or its third-party service providers may transfer personal data to countries
            outside your country of residence, including outside the European Economic Area (EEA). Where
            applicable law requires safeguards for international transfers, the Service Provider will use
            appropriate mechanisms, such as:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs) approved by the European Commission</li>
            <li>Adequacy decisions or other legally recognized transfer mechanisms</li>
            <li>Your consent, where required and legally permitted</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Data protection laws in other countries may differ from those in your jurisdiction. Where required by
            law, the Service Provider will apply appropriate safeguards and obtain any consent required for the
            transfer.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Your Rights</h2>
          <p>
            You may request access to, correction of, or deletion of personal data held by the Service Provider.
            To exercise these rights, or to withdraw consent where processing is based on consent, contact the
            Service Provider at
            <a href="mailto:contact@loefstudio.com">contact@loefstudio.com</a>.
          </p>
          <p>
            Because the Application has no accounts, the Service Provider may be unable to identify data relating
            to you without additional information such as your advertising identifier. In that case, the Service
            Provider may ask you for details needed to locate the relevant data, or explain why the request cannot
            be fulfilled.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Your California Privacy Rights (CCPA/CPRA)</h2>
          <p>
            If you are a California resident, you have the right to know what personal information is collected,
            the right to delete personal information, the right to opt out of the sale or sharing of personal
            information, and the right to non-discrimination for exercising these rights.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Service Provider does not sell your personal information for money. However, the use of
            advertising identifiers for personalized advertising may be considered "sharing" for cross-context
            behavioral advertising under the CCPA/CPRA. You may opt out by declining the App Tracking Transparency
            prompt, by enabling <strong>Limit Ad Tracking</strong> in your device settings, or by contacting the
            Service Provider at
            <a href="mailto:contact@loefstudio.com">contact@loefstudio.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Opt-Out Rights</h2>
          <p>
            You can stop further collection of information from your mobile device by uninstalling the
            Application. Uninstalling will stop the Application from collecting data from your device, but it does
            not automatically delete information that has already been transmitted to the Service Provider or to
            third parties.
          </p>
          <p>
            To request deletion of your personal data, to withdraw consent, or to exercise any of your rights,
            contact the Service Provider at
            <a href="mailto:contact@loefstudio.com">contact@loefstudio.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Data Retention Policy</h2>
          <p>The Service Provider retains personal data based on its necessity for the stated purposes:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>
              <strong>Automatically Collected Data:</strong> Retained for up to 24 months from collection, unless
              longer retention is required for legal compliance
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Purchase and Subscription Records:</strong> Retained as long as required for tax, accounting,
              and legal compliance purposes
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Aggregated and Anonymized Data:</strong> Retained indefinitely as it no longer identifies you
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong>Data required for legal compliance:</strong> Retained as long as required by applicable law
            </li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            You may request deletion of your personal data, subject to any legal obligation to retain it. To make
            such a request, please contact the Service Provider at
            <a href="mailto:contact@loefstudio.com">contact@loefstudio.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Children</h2>
          <p>
            The Application is not directed to children under 13 years of age, or such higher age as required by
            applicable law. The Service Provider does not knowingly solicit data from children or market the
            Application to them, and does not knowingly collect personally identifiable information from children
            in violation of applicable law.
          </p>
          <p>
            Where parental or guardian consent is required under applicable law, the Application is not intended
            for use without that consent. In the event the Service Provider discovers that a child has provided
            personal information, the Service Provider will delete this from their servers. If you are a parent or
            guardian and you are aware that your child has provided the Service Provider with personal
            information, please contact the Service Provider at
            <a href="mailto:contact@loefstudio.com">contact@loefstudio.com</a>
            so that they will be able to take the necessary actions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Security</h2>
          <p>
            The Service Provider is concerned about safeguarding the confidentiality of your information. The
            Service Provider provides physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards to protect information the
            Service Provider processes and maintains.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Data Breach Notification</h2>
          <p>
            If a data breach occurs that affects your personal data, the Service Provider will notify you in
            accordance with applicable legal requirements, including, where required, providing information about
            the nature of the breach and the steps being taken to address it.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Changes</h2>
          <p>
            The Service Provider may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. The Service Provider will
            notify you of material changes by posting the updated Privacy Policy with an effective date. Where
            required by law, the Service Provider will seek your consent to material changes before they take
            effect.
          </p>
          <p>
            Previous versions of this Privacy Policy will be maintained and made available upon request by
            contacting the Service Provider at
            <a href="mailto:contact@loefstudio.com">contact@loefstudio.com</a>.
          </p>
          <p>This Privacy Policy is effective as of {effectiveDate}.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Your Consent</h2>
          <p>
            Where processing is based on consent, you provide that consent by affirmatively opting in to the
            relevant feature or action. You may withdraw consent at any time without affecting processing carried
            out before withdrawal. Processing based on other lawful bases is carried out as described above.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2>Contact Us</h2>
          <p>
            If you have any questions regarding privacy while using the Application, or have questions about these
            practices, please contact the Service Provider via email at
            <a href="mailto:contact@loefstudio.com">contact@loefstudio.com</a>.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </div>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .policy-page {
    padding-top: 140px;
    padding-bottom: 6rem;
    background: radial-gradient(circle at 10% 0%, rgba(255, 107, 155, 0.05) 0%, rgba(78, 202, 255, 0.04) 45%, hsl(var(--bg-cream)) 100%);
  }

  .policy-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: hsl(var(--accent-pink));
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    font-family: 'Fredoka', sans-serif;
  }

  .policy-title {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  }

  .section-line {
    width: 45px;
    height: 4px;
    background: var(--gradient-jewel);
    margin: 0 auto;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .policy-meta {
    margin-top: 1.2rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: hsl(var(--text-muted));
  }

  .policy-card {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3.5rem;
  }

  /* Static legal document: no lift on hover */
  .policy-card:hover {
    transform: none;
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-soft);
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.85;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
  }

  .policy-card section {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
  }

  .policy-card h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin-bottom: 0.9rem;
    color: hsl(var(--text-primary));
  }

  .policy-card p {
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .policy-card p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .policy-card ul {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
  }

  .policy-card li {
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: hsl(var(--text-secondary));
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .policy-card li::marker {
    color: hsl(var(--accent-pink));
  }

  .policy-card strong {
    color: hsl(var(--text-primary));
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .policy-card a {
    color: hsl(var(--accent-pink));
    text-decoration: none;
    font-weight: 600;
    word-break: break-word;
    border-bottom: 1px solid hsla(var(--accent-pink), 0.25);
    transition: var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .policy-card a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: hsl(var(--accent-pink));
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .policy-page {
      padding-top: 110px;
    }

    .policy-card {
      padding: 1.8rem 1.4rem;
      border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    }
  }
</style>
